Some state governors elected on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC) met with President Muhammadu Buhari at the Presidential Villa, Abuja, on Wednesday morning. The meeting was the second in two days. Those at Wednesday’s meeting were – Abdulazeez Yari (Zamfara), Simon Lalong (Plateau), Rochas Okorocha (Imo), Abdullahi Ganduje (Kano) and Ibikunle Amosun (Ogun). The governors resolved at the meeting to support the President’s position on election of new party executives at the expiration of the current officers’ tenure. Details later…